message: right up till 1993 they had platinum albums; not just up till 1985 like the old wording suggests; accuracy seems to be tertiary to being "easy to read" here.
NO ONE consideres Vapour Trails or Snakes and Arrows more signficant than The Farewell to Kings.

Binksternet keeps adding incorrect info.  Please stop it.  It should be reviewed if you keep doing it and you should be blocked. 2112 was their first top 5 album, their breakthrough, and should be kept.  New World Man was not a global hit - it was only a hit in North America.  Why do you keep putting incorrect information in? Closer to the Heart has more sales than Fly by Night - read the article!!!

/* Current state of the lead */ Spirit of Radio is on the Rock Hall of Fames 500 songs that changed rock.  Tom Sawyer was not a 4x platinum seller - Moving Pictures was - this again shows Binksternets propensity to put incorrect informaton in.  Please stop it.
mentioning the multi-part nature of 2112 is integral - that is what their progressive rock period was most known for.

Can we please leave in some indication of how big certain bands were (in this case Rush) at their peak?  A number 3 album in the US and UK is a big deal.  So is selling 4x platinum.  I think most casual readers want to know about a band's key songs, esp. the onces I added are inducted in the Canadian Songwriters Hall of Fame, Tom Sawyer is world renowned, and Spirit of Radio is in the list of songs that shaped R and R, plus New World Man was a No. 1 hit in Canada.  Who cares about hiatuses?

a number one single in the US is very signficiant and should be mentioned in the lead.  It is usually mentioned in leads for most bands and should be mentioned in lead for the album - it is their only US number one song.

chartmasters was only the source for the 6X platinum date in the US and the total worldwide sales of 12 million.  The chart data is commonly known and is in the article.  Have just gone with commonly known 5X platinum US status.  Total sales of 12 million now has another source as entered.

the success of the re-release of Dream On was essential to Aerosmith's breaking into the mainstream - if you were alive then you know that.  Cut some other excessive wording and the cultural phenom statement is clearly outside the sphere of music and would need to be explicitly references as it is biased and an overstatement.
is standard to mention 5 or 6 of their most important singles - Mama and That's All qualify as that.

many articles state if an artist had 5 or 6 or 8 straight number one albums in a major market; many state their first US top ten LP, many state what the biggest seller (in X platinum) was in the US; Should state whether other songs were successful from Invisbile Touch in other countries - not just a US website.

as I explained before, they had charted in the UK before Foxtrot - this statement is wrong.  The only success they had in mainland Europe was Italy - the current statment is wrong,  I do not care if it is FA if is is wrong.  I note that you cited this as wrong that I had not even added - it was wrong before.  The focus on the US for Invisible Touch LP is wrong - Wikipedia is not just a US website.  Be logical not just emotion that your article can and should be improved.
correcting incorrrect info; previous had charted, just not highly. no data supports their charting higher in Europe first aside form Italy for Foxtrot.
trimmed a bit of length - the lead is still 5 or 6 longer than the leads for Led Zepplin, the Who and the Stones - seems out of line.

once again, adding Bogar emphasizes she essentially help three huge stars of the era win their only Oscars, plus starred with another big star from the era (Grant) multiple times.  This is very important part of her legacy, and shows she was better than the men in many or most respects.
her lead is shorter than other actors of similar statue

these additions are warranted; sit back and read and think about it; it is always talked about who an actor starred with and whether they brought out the best in others, which Hepburn did - that is an essential part of her legacy as was her partnerships with Grant and Tracy - you have to mention specific movies with Tracy.  Leave this alone.  No one else object months last year or weeks now.  Leave it alone.

cut clear inconcise text that is not needed - lead is way too long.

this lead is much shorter than Martin Scorcese; mentioning some frequent collaborateurs is done often and is warranted given the legendary status of some of Hitchcock's and the importance of the performers.  Plus that paragraph was strangely truncated.
link calling them rock superstars is now dead.  Better to leave reference from Davis book in.

the Birds is recognized as the first modern disaster movie and it was even spoofed on Saturday Night Live a month ago 60 years after its release!  Its the only one of those on the Congress Presevation List not listed elsewherein the Lead.  This addition is warranted.

it is VERY common for the lead on an actor or director to state the total number of nominations the artist had; only randomly mentioning different noniminations throughout the lead without adding it up is inconsistent.  I hope the other editor will read some other leads before reversing this very valid and logical change.
deleted over-statement as that chart success is not that much.
Given her Nordic beauty status if seems sensible to mention her three largest romantic co-leads.

I do not mean to irrritate anyone, but it seems to be adding so many second tier films has made the lead too long compared to other actors of similar stature - Grant, Stewart, K. Hepburn; so I deleted a few.  Her getting nom for Baby Jane and Crawford not is legendary and should be in, in my opinion..
unless I am mistaken (and I have visited there several times) the park is not just a theme park; maybe part of it was in the 60s but not all of it was.

Wikipedia is not just for US and UK readers; chart positons in Australia and Europe are relevant as they show whether a band is successful world-wide not just in North American and perhaps the UK (for example, Eagles are mostly only a NA success unlike a Rod Stewart or a Bryan Adams being world-wide successes).
this info is already provided in the lead so it makes sense to have at least this much detail in the body.
